<TITLE> UN, Germany, Switzerland greet Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 8 (bdnews24.com)  UN secretary-general Ban Ki-moon on Thursday congratulated Sheikh Hasina on her becoming prime minister for a second stint. German chancellor Angela Markel and Swiss President Hans-Rudolf Merz also greeted Hasina. "In a letter, Ban Ki-moon greeted Sheikh Hasina for getting elected Bangladesh's prime minister," said a government handout. The handout, issued by the Press Information Department (PID), said Ban thanked Hasina for working with the political parties to strengthen democratic process in Bangladesh. The UN chief also thanked Bangladeshis for holding peaceful elections. "Please accept my warm congratulations on your appointment as Prime Minister of the People's Republic of Bangladesh," Markel said in her letter sent to Hasina, according to a Thursday press statement issued by German embassy. She said: "I look forward to further developing the relationship of trust and cooperation between our countries with you. "Germany will continue to be a reliable partner to Bangladesh as it works to strengthen democracy, the rule of law and human rights." According to a press statement of the Swiss embassy in Dhaka, Merz, the Switzerland president, said, "I would like to extend my best wishes to you for your personal well-being and the future prosperity of your country". "The recent elections are an important milestone in the history of Bangladesh. "On this special occasion, the Swiss government reiterates its commitment to continue its support to the democratic, social and economic development in Bangladesh'', the statement quoted the president as saying.
